00:13:13,725 --> 00:13:15,317
We all wished he could be there.

243
00:13:15,427 --> 00:13:17,190
But we knew why he was running.

244
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:19,990
One of the things Markoff
hadn't mentioned in his article...

245
00:13:20,099 --> 00:13:22,465
was the eight months
of solitary confinement.

246
00:13:22,567 --> 00:13:25,730
The guy was in solitary confinement
for eight months.

247
00:13:28,038 --> 00:13:29,096
Think about it.

248
00:13:29,206 --> 00:13:32,836
I mean, that would definitely change a man.

249
00:13:32,945 --> 00:13:34,706
You would run.You wouldn't want that.

250
00:13:34,812 --> 00:13:39,114
It was eight months, not for anything he did,
but because the judge was scared.

251
00:13:39,216 --> 00:13:41,778
And if you get someone
who is that unaware...

252
00:13:41,885 --> 00:13:44,980
of actually what he can do
and thinks he can destroy the world.

253
00:13:45,322 --> 00:13:47,451
If you have someone
who has enough power...

254
00:13:47,558 --> 00:13:49,994
to put you in solitary confinement
you will run.

255
00:13:50,095 --> 00:13:51,426
It makes perfect sense to me.

256
00:13:51,528 --> 00:13:53,519
I think it's part hype...

257
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:58,268
part hysteria, part lack of understanding...

258
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:00,663
and part fear.

259
00:14:00,773 --> 00:14:03,365
Solitary confinement means no books...

260
00:14:03,475 --> 00:14:05,841
no pencil, no paper, no company.

261
00:14:06,110 --> 00:14:07,874
Nothing to do...

262
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:10,947
but stare at these small four walls.

263
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:14,043
He would get out one hour a day..

264
00:14:15,153 --> 00:14:16,211
and that's it.

265
00:14:16,322 --> 00:14:19,312
You know, he might whistle up
some missile launch codes.

266
00:14:19,423 --> 00:14:21,325
That's a big problem
with hackers nowadays.

267
00:14:21,427 --> 00:14:25,158
They get a little pissed off
and they launch some nukes by whistling.

268
00:14:25,562 --> 00:14:27,464
The fear factor is just insane.

269
00:14:27,566 --> 00:14:30,625
Once or twice or maybe more,
I can't even remember...

270
00:14:30,735 --> 00:14:33,899
they didn't even bring him down
to the visitors' room.

271
00:14:34,004 --> 00:14:36,235
They took my daughter and I...

272
00:14:36,341 --> 00:14:39,436
upstairs to a floor...

273
00:14:39,543 --> 00:14:41,909
that wasn't occupied at that time.

274
00:14:42,014 --> 00:14:44,846
We were the only ones there and the guard.

275
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:46,850
They were hovering over him...

276
00:14:46,951 --> 00:14:50,216
as though he was an absolute monster

277
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:53,846
What could he possibly do, you know?

278
00:14:55,094 --> 00:14:56,652
Could he make...

279
00:14:58,096 --> 00:15:00,394
a computer out of the telephone?

280
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:04,659
I don't know what they were afraid of!

281
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:07,302
First of all, he had no desire to.

282
00:15:07,404 --> 00:15:09,931
Secondly, it wouldn't have
accomplished anything.

283
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:12,100
Thirdly, he couldn't do it.

284
00:15:13,445 --> 00:15:16,538
Kevin managed to elude the authorities
into the next year.

285
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:19,379
Then, on February 15, 1995...

286
00:15:19,652 --> 00:15:22,052
they found him in Raleigh, North Carolina.

287
00:15:22,153 --> 00:15:26,022
The FBI's most-wanted computer hacker
is behind bars.

288
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:29,591
Kevin Mitnick was jailed without bond
in Raleigh, North Carolina...

289
00:15:29,695 --> 00:15:31,822
where he was arrested this week.

290
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:35,365
He's accused of breaking into
corporate computers nationwide.

291
00:15:35,466 --> 00:15:39,426
Private computer experts say
so many other hackers are at work...

292
00:15:39,538 --> 00:15:41,768
that privacy is virtually impossible.

293
00:15:42,441 --> 00:15:44,202
The FBI had managed to track Kevin...

294
00:15:44,308 --> 00:15:47,745
with the help of a mysterious
computer expert, Tsutomu Shimomura...

295
00:15:47,846 --> 00:15:50,110
who, along with some friends
had managed to track...

296
00:15:50,215 --> 00:15:53,378
Kevin's cellular phone signal
to the apartment he was staying in.

297
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:57,279
One of Shimomura's friends who was there
while the signal was being traced...

298
00:15:57,389 --> 00:15:59,322
was none other than John Markoff...

299
00:15:59,423 --> 00:16:02,120
who wrote an even bigger
front page story this time.

300
00:16:02,225 --> 00:16:05,456
Sure enough, I opened the door,
the next day...

301
00:16:05,798 --> 00:16:09,325
to the hotel room,
and there was The Times outside the door.

302
00:16:09,634 --> 00:16:12,604
And I picked it up and I just thought,
''Oh, my God.''

303
00:16:13,937 --> 00:16:17,340
This article had a new list of things
that Kevin had supposedly done...

304
00:16:17,442 --> 00:16:20,469
including breaking into
Shimomura's ultra-secure computer...

305
00:16:20,577 --> 00:16:22,604
leaving nasty voice mail messages...

306
00:16:22,715 --> 00:16:25,615
and stealing 20,000 credit card numbers...

307
00:16:25,783 --> 00:16:29,777
something that was mentioned
in the first paragraph on the front page.

308
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:32,879
But 13 paragraphs later, on Page D17...

309
00:16:33,192 --> 00:16:35,524
it was revealed that he had never used
any of them.

310
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:38,822
They were credit card numbers
that had been left lying around...

311
00:16:38,931 --> 00:16:41,899
by Internet Service Provider Netcom
for almost a year.

312
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,332
Netcom credit card file,
everybody had that file.

313
00:16:45,437 --> 00:16:47,769
If you didn't have that file, you were a loser.

314
00:16:47,873 --> 00:16:51,399
Hundreds of people had that,
they swapped it around like bubble gum.

315
00:16:51,509 --> 00:16:55,139
And then they claim that he's the one
who did it, he's the one that had it...

316
00:16:55,245 --> 00:16:58,976
when that was floating around for months
before he theoretically had it.

317
00:16:59,082 --> 00:17:01,880
Everybody and his sister's
got a million credit card numbers.

318
00:17:01,985 --> 00:17:05,479
What's the big deal?
It's a meaningless thing to have.

319
00:17:06,592 --> 00:17:08,558
What I want to know...

320
00:17:09,428 --> 00:17:11,487
is did he threaten anybody in any way?

321
00:17:11,596 --> 00:17:14,430
Did he claim he was going to do
some particular set of harm?

322
00:17:14,531 --> 00:17:18,025
Are there any notebooks
that showed he had plans...

323
00:17:18,237 --> 00:17:22,695
to conspire to commit any particular thing...

324
00:17:22,906 --> 00:17:25,067
other than humiliating
Tsutomu Shimomura...

325
00:17:25,175 --> 00:17:28,374
which any idiot who's ever met Shimomura
could have told him...

326
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,913
this was not the guy to mess with.

327
00:17:31,048 --> 00:17:32,517
I met Shimomura once.

328
00:17:32,616 --> 00:17:35,483
The first time I met Shimomura
was in front of Congress.

329
00:17:35,586 --> 00:17:38,317
And I was testifying
to a congressional subcommittee...

330
00:17:38,423 --> 00:17:40,255
and there's this guy...

331
00:17:40,357 --> 00:17:44,227
in sandals and, like, ragged-ass cutofs.

332
00:17:44,327 --> 00:17:46,261
And the rest of us are done up in ties...

333
00:17:46,365 --> 00:17:48,833
it's me and theAttorney General
from New Jersey.

334
00:17:48,932 --> 00:17:52,893
And we're sitting there, giving our best
''Yes, we're in front of Congress'' thing.

335
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:57,269
And Shimomura is there in this surfer gear.

336
00:17:57,375 --> 00:18:00,277
And he pulls thisAT&T cell phone...

337
00:18:00,711 --> 00:18:03,770
pulls it out of the shrink-wrap,
finger-hacks it...

338
00:18:03,882 --> 00:18:06,009
and starts monitoring phone calls...

339
00:18:06,116 --> 00:18:08,018
going up and down Capitol Hill...

340
00:18:08,118 --> 00:18:12,056
while an FBI agent
is standing at his shoulder listening to him.

341
00:18:12,289 --> 00:18:16,227
I'm like, ''This fucker's got balls
the size of durian fruit.''

342
00:18:16,428 --> 00:18:20,057
You know, this is unbelievable.
This is the heaviest guy I've ever seen.

343
00:18:21,231 --> 00:18:23,028
I mean, he's hacking, right?

344
00:18:23,134 --> 00:18:26,104
He was finger-hacking this phone
in front of Congress...

345
00:18:26,203 --> 00:18:30,642
with two FBI agents
and John Gage from Sun Microsystems...

346
00:18:30,740 --> 00:18:33,971
in the room with him.And I was like,
''Wow,'' you know.

347
00:18:34,077 --> 00:18:35,478
I mean, I was impressed.

348
00:18:35,579 --> 00:18:38,548
Inside of a week, Shimomura and Markoff
had signed a book deal...

349
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:41,413
estimated to be worth $750,000.

350
00:18:41,553 --> 00:18:44,817
It would be another 19 months
before Kevin would even be indicted.

351
00:18:44,923 --> 00:18:48,381
The book, entitled Takedown,
was finished by the end of the year.

352
00:18:48,692 --> 00:18:50,855
When I read it, I was aghast.

353
00:18:52,529 --> 00:18:56,557
It was Tsutomu's
eating and skateboarding habits.

354
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:59,835
I'd been to a lot of the restaurants
he'd been to...

355
00:18:59,938 --> 00:19:02,736
but I didn't need a hacker book
to tell me about them.

356
00:19:02,839 --> 00:19:04,397
Takedown. Well....

357
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:09,376
I don't what I want to say about Takedown.

358
00:19:10,615 --> 00:19:12,913
Takedown was not well received.

359
00:19:16,887 --> 00:19:19,881
1996 came and went as did 1997.

360
00:19:20,057 --> 00:19:22,583
Kevin remained in prison
without even a bail hearing...

361
00:19:22,692 --> 00:19:25,355
and no prospect of a trial anytime soon.

362
00:19:26,096 --> 00:19:28,826
A25-count indictment
accused him of nothing more serious...

363
00:19:28,932 --> 00:19:31,095
than lying on the telephone
about who he was...

364
00:19:31,201 --> 00:19:34,468
and copying software which he
never tried to sell or even distribute.

365
00:19:34,573 --> 00:19:36,803
Nothing about hacking
into Shimomura's machine...

366
00:19:36,909 --> 00:19:39,036
or having 20,000 credit card numbers...

367
00:19:39,144 --> 00:19:42,442
nothing that would have appeared
in a John Markoff story.

368
00:19:43,448 --> 00:19:47,111
North Carolina had also charged him
with making free cellular phone calls.

369
00:19:47,219 --> 00:19:48,980
Kevin was given a two-year sentence...

370
00:19:49,086 --> 00:19:51,248
more than he would have gotten
for manslaughter.

371
00:19:51,355 --> 00:19:54,018
But the federal charges still remained.

372
00:19:54,491 --> 00:19:56,688
They even put him
in solitary confinement again...

373
00:19:56,795 --> 00:20:00,891
because the authorities were convinced
he'd build a transmitter out of a Walkman...

374
00:20:00,999 --> 00:20:04,400
sneak into the warden's office
and monitor his conversations.

375
00:20:04,501 --> 00:20:06,560
The mainstream media made light of it...

376
00:20:06,672 --> 00:20:10,005
claiming Mitnick was put in solitary
for having too many cans of tuna.

377
00:20:10,106 --> 00:20:12,736
What everyone seemed to forget
was years were going by...

378
00:20:12,844 --> 00:20:14,778
and this guy had yet to be tried.

379
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:17,440
And then, things got a whole lot worse.

380
00:20:17,548 --> 00:20:17,615
June 1998.

381
00:20:17,615 --> 00:20:19,317
June 1998.

382
00:20:19,317 --> 00:20:21,876
A movie version of Takedown
was announced.

383
00:20:21,987 --> 00:20:24,421
Skeet Ulrich, who played a killer in Scream...

384
00:20:24,521 --> 00:20:25,785
was set to play Kevin Mitnick.

385
00:20:25,891 --> 00:20:27,825
And Russell Wong
from The Joy Luck Club...

386
00:20:27,924 --> 00:20:29,721
would be Tsutomu Shimomura.

387
00:20:29,826 --> 00:20:31,384
It didn't seem to matter to anyone...

388
00:20:31,496 --> 00:20:34,759
that the real-life Kevin
was still rotting in prison without a trial.

389
00:20:34,865 --> 00:20:37,096
According to the script
we got our hands on...

390
00:20:37,201 --> 00:20:39,692
he had been found guilty
and sentenced already.

391
00:20:39,805 --> 00:20:41,295
The magic of Hollywood.

392
00:20:42,339 --> 00:20:44,204
They even brought
Kevin and Tsutomu closer.

393
00:20:44,307 --> 00:20:47,210
In real life, they'd only met
for a few seconds in a courtroom.

394
00:20:47,310 --> 00:20:49,746
In the Hollywood version
they met in a dark alleyway...

395
00:20:49,846 --> 00:20:52,337
where Kevin would proceed
to bash Tsutomu on the head...

396
00:20:52,451 --> 00:20:53,816
with a garbage can lid.

397
00:20:54,117 --> 00:20:56,644
We had to tell the world
that this was a big mistake.

398
00:20:56,755 --> 00:20:58,482
The truth needed to be told.

399
00:20:58,588 --> 00:21:01,150
And we could either do it ourselves,
or use the media.

400
00:21:01,259 --> 00:21:03,854
That's right, the media,
democracy's biggest allies...

401
00:21:03,961 --> 00:21:06,487
committed to informing the public
no matter the cost.

402
00:21:06,596 --> 00:21:08,190
The true conscience of America.

403
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:11,932
-Stop pushing!
-Get out of the way, Brad.

404
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:15,096
Watch yourselves!

405
00:21:16,406 --> 00:21:18,375
Come on, guys.

406
00:21:19,743 --> 00:21:21,711
Don't yell at me, everyone's in front of me.

407
00:21:21,813 --> 00:21:23,472
Tell them to come back.

408
00:21:23,582 --> 00:21:25,777
He's coming to the mike!

409
00:21:28,318 --> 00:21:30,288
Would you guys get down?

410
00:21:35,692 --> 00:21:37,355
Watch the mikes!

411
00:21:38,497 --> 00:21:40,192
Let's get out of the way.

412
00:21:45,201 --> 00:21:46,170
Come on.

413
00:21:54,211 --> 00:21:56,112
We decided to do it ourselves.

414
00:21:56,279 --> 00:21:59,339
We found Skeet Ulrich's apartment
in New York in a phone book...

415
00:21:59,451 --> 00:22:01,781
and paid a visit
to try and get him the real story

416
00:22:01,885 --> 00:22:02,854
But he had moved.

417
00:22:02,952 --> 00:22:07,152
I know, because the doorman let me
look at every single name in the book.

418
00:22:07,692 --> 00:22:10,526
So the next stop was Miramax Films
on the West Side.

419
00:22:10,627 --> 00:22:14,429
We figured they'd appreciate a chance
to correct the mistakes in the screenplay.

420
00:22:14,531 --> 00:22:17,400
And we knew we'd be warmly received
because this was Miramax.

421
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:20,130
The company had distributed
Michael Moore's latest film...

422
00:22:20,238 --> 00:22:22,761
you know, the guy
who films in everybody's lobby.

423
00:22:27,711 --> 00:22:29,906
Hi, we're looking for Miramax?

424
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:34,076
-What's your name?
-Emmanuel Goldstein.

425
00:22:34,184 --> 00:22:35,173
Who you here to see?

426
00:22:35,287 --> 00:22:37,185
Sorry, you can't film in here.

427
00:22:37,855 --> 00:22:40,221
-You can't film here?
-No, it's a landmark.

428
00:22:40,325 --> 00:22:41,758
Sorry, you can't....

429
00:22:41,858 --> 00:22:45,021
So there's no way you can call upstairs....

430
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:48,798
You have to call them, they will call me.

431
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:51,731
This wasn't going well.

432
00:22:51,970 --> 00:22:54,438
How could a movie company
tell us to stop filming?

433
00:22:54,538 --> 00:22:56,403
All we wanted to do was talk to somebody.

434
00:23:00,144 --> 00:23:01,269
What a letdown.

435
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:03,641
His light is on, so he's capturing everything.

436
00:23:03,749 --> 00:23:06,615
So please go outside
before he has to call the police.

437
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:09,585
All right, we don't want that,
so we'll go outside....

438
00:23:09,921 --> 00:23:13,184
We called the office and waited
to hear from them, but we never did.

439
00:23:13,289 --> 00:23:16,952
It was like they were scared of us.
Maybe they agreed with Bill Clinton...

440
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:19,997
that hackers were as one-dimensional
as they were in the script.

441
00:23:20,096 --> 00:23:21,998
How could we get them
to see the other side?

442
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:26,836
That night, NewYork City
introduced unlimited ride MetroCards.

443
00:23:26,938 --> 00:23:30,066
We decided to find out
how long it would take for our cards to reset...

444
00:23:30,173 --> 00:23:32,539
so we could let people in for free.

445
00:23:40,683 --> 00:23:43,174
This is what the hacker world
was really all about.

446
00:23:43,288 --> 00:23:44,721
Why didn't they see this?

447
00:23:44,823 --> 00:23:48,416
Why did it always have to be something evil
to the people who didn't get it?

448
00:23:52,962 --> 00:23:54,363
We had only one option.

449
00:23:54,531 --> 00:23:56,592
''For Off The Hook,
I recently heard the show...

450
00:23:56,701 --> 00:23:59,192
''where you got the copy of a script
for Takedown.

451
00:23:59,304 --> 00:24:02,603
''I found it really amusing
howthe scriptwriters can take the truth...

452
00:24:02,707 --> 00:24:06,643
''and not twist it or fabricate it,
but just plain lie about what happened.''

453
00:24:07,010 --> 00:24:10,573
I've heard about Kevin's story,
and thanks to Off The Hook...

454
00:24:10,682 --> 00:24:13,173
I heard about this meeting,
and I decided to come...

455
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:14,615
and see how I can help.

456
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:17,618
It wasn't from me, it's from somebody else,
I knew who that is.

457
00:24:17,721 --> 00:24:21,852
-ls there a good catchiness?
-Yeah. ''From Supermax to Miramax:

458
00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:24,457
''Three-and-a-halfYears With No Trial.''

459
00:24:25,261 --> 00:24:29,063
And then you can make another one,
''From Miramax to Supermax:

460
00:24:30,201 --> 00:24:31,362
''And No Trial.''

461
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:34,439
When they see two ''Free Kevin'' stickers...

462
00:24:34,538 --> 00:24:39,134
when they see 10, 20, 100,
they're gonna say, ''Who the hell is Kevin?''

463
00:24:39,242 --> 00:24:41,608
They'll keep saying it
until somebody answers them.

464
00:24:41,711 --> 00:24:45,547
One or two people that know more about it
are one or two people more on our side.

465
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:48,881
Those two people get two people
who get two people.That's how it is.

466
00:24:48,987 --> 00:24:51,285
We're gonna be in their face
every step of the way.

467
00:24:51,387 --> 00:24:54,721
If it comes to showing this thing
on the screen, in theaters...

468
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:56,519
we're going to be there, too.

469
00:24:56,626 --> 00:25:00,086
I mean, what we're doing now
isn't going to be finished...

470
00:25:00,198 --> 00:25:03,133
until Kevin has his trial, until Kevin is out.

471
00:25:03,233 --> 00:25:05,634
''Guilty by Hollywood''
or something like that.

472
00:25:05,737 --> 00:25:08,035
-That's a good one.
-I like that.

473
00:25:09,105 --> 00:25:11,701
Yeah, I did look at the script, and....

474
00:25:12,041 --> 00:25:13,101
I don't know.

475
00:25:13,211 --> 00:25:17,509
It's a shame and it definitely
shouldn't be something out there...

476
00:25:17,615 --> 00:25:20,105
for someone
who knows very little about Kevin...

477
00:25:20,218 --> 00:25:24,211
to then see this movie
and have ideas in their head that are untrue.

478
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:27,118
We had tried talking to them
and they wouldn't listen.

479
00:25:27,223 --> 00:25:31,025
Now, by having a demonstration outside
their offices, they would have to listen.

480
00:25:31,127 --> 00:25:33,857
But we were hackers.
What did we know about demonstrations?

481
00:25:33,963 --> 00:25:35,557
Just that they can turn into riots...

482
00:25:35,665 --> 00:25:38,727
especially when the Mayor
bans demonstrations outside City Hall...

483
00:25:38,836 --> 00:25:41,169
and the cops shoot people a lot more.

484
00:25:41,337 --> 00:25:44,307
We needed guidance,
someone with experience.

485
00:25:44,509 --> 00:25:46,567
We looked all over town for an activist.

486
00:25:46,678 --> 00:25:49,738
Maybe one of those gray-haired hippies
from the '60s.

487
00:25:49,846 --> 00:25:52,009
We found one. Sort of.

488
00:26:02,559 --> 00:26:05,257
What's it like demonstrating here?
Do you get harassed?

489
00:26:05,363 --> 00:26:08,490
They hate our guts because
they don't want the truth to come out.

490
00:26:08,598 --> 00:26:11,260
Why do you think there isn't more activism?

491
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:14,269
Because people don't care, they're scared...

492
00:26:14,471 --> 00:26:18,634
they're afraid they'll get into trouble.
I can understand it.

493
00:26:18,741 --> 00:26:21,608
But we still have to take a stand,
afraid or not.

494
00:26:21,711 --> 00:26:24,703
We have to at least give it a try,
we have to give it a shot.

495
00:26:24,816 --> 00:26:28,775
-Has this cop been giving you any trouble?
-No, he hasn't bothered me.

496
00:26:28,885 --> 00:26:32,323
And we have a President
that wants to suck their brains out.

497
00:26:32,958 --> 00:26:34,892
That bothers a lot of people, but....

498
00:26:34,991 --> 00:26:39,894
Anybody that's decent gets bothered
when a little child is tortured to death.

499
00:26:40,096 --> 00:26:42,498
Or when a President
is sucking their brains out.

500
00:26:42,601 --> 00:26:43,863
Yeah.

501
00:26:44,067 --> 00:26:46,058
He wasn't exactly what we had in mind.

502
00:26:46,171 --> 00:26:49,402
I got a real earful about
the evils of homosexuals and communists.

503
00:26:49,507 --> 00:26:52,806
But in the end,
he told us the one thing we needed to hear

504
00:26:52,911 --> 00:26:56,174
When you demonstrate,
make sure you're in the right.

505
00:26:56,548 --> 00:27:00,038
And that's the one thing we were sure of:
We were right.

506
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:06,314
The day arrived.
We had no idea what to expect.

507
00:27:12,462 --> 00:27:15,022
We just stood there for a while,
not knowing what to do.

508
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:17,656
Our converted phone company van
got more attention than us.

509
00:27:17,769 --> 00:27:19,930
My name is Noah Kenickstein,
I'm an attorney.

510
00:27:20,038 --> 00:27:22,903
-For Miramax?
-No. For you all!

511
00:27:23,008 --> 00:27:24,566
I didn't even know.

512
00:27:24,674 --> 00:27:28,337
-I'm a lawyer. I'm representing you all.
-Okay. Great.

513
00:27:28,680 --> 00:27:31,579
So, no one's getting arrested, right?

514
00:27:31,914 --> 00:27:34,076
-I didn't plan on it.
-Good.

515
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:37,112
The National Lawyers Guild
sent someone to protect us...

516
00:27:37,221 --> 00:27:38,915
and that was the turning point.

517
00:27:39,022 --> 00:27:42,423
Things began to come together.
Even members of the media showed up.

518
00:27:42,527 --> 00:27:46,054
It seemed like everyone except Miramax
was taking this seriously.

519
00:27:46,730 --> 00:27:50,758
We learned that when you stand outside
a film studio's offices with picket signs...

520
00:27:50,867 --> 00:27:52,028
people notice.

521
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:04,611
These folks are gonna
put on a little demonstration here.

522
00:28:04,714 --> 00:28:07,583
They're gonna be marching around.
I thought I would tell you.

523
00:28:07,684 --> 00:28:09,846
-You could tell the....
-I'll tell the precinct.

524
00:28:09,952 --> 00:28:13,820
Tell the precinct, and tell them I'm a lawyer
It's nice and calm.

525
00:28:14,125 --> 00:28:15,922
No problems at all.

526
00:28:16,027 --> 00:28:19,019
But they're having a little....
They'll be marching around.

527
00:28:19,130 --> 00:28:21,028
-I've got it.
-I wanted to tell you that.

528
00:28:21,132 --> 00:28:24,588
I appreciate thatvery much.
Could you tell me approximately how many?

529
00:28:24,701 --> 00:28:28,432
I would say there's gonna be....
50 people, Patty?

530
00:28:29,240 --> 00:28:32,173
50 to 60, maximum 50.

531
00:28:35,144 --> 00:28:39,308
-What area are you doing it in?
-ln front of Miramax Films.

532
00:28:39,415 --> 00:28:42,284
They're demonstrating about a movie
that they're making.

533
00:28:42,385 --> 00:28:44,651
Thanks a lot, I appreciate you stopping me.

534
00:28:44,756 --> 00:28:46,189
Everybody's nice and calm.

535
00:28:46,289 --> 00:28:49,852
-I'll tell them that. Thanks for the advice.
-Okay, no problem.

536
00:28:50,693 --> 00:28:52,959
No, they're not gonna come on purpose.

537
00:28:53,064 --> 00:28:54,723
People are, you know....

538
00:28:54,932 --> 00:28:57,627
You're talking about suits.

539
00:28:57,736 --> 00:29:00,671
They don't give a fuck.
You got to go hand it to them.

540
00:29:00,770 --> 00:29:03,000
Don't harass the people who walk by

541
00:29:03,106 --> 00:29:05,633
Some people have crises
going on in their lives.

542
00:29:05,742 --> 00:29:08,233
They can't be bothered with our problems.

543
00:29:09,078 --> 00:29:12,948
Do you have a permit?
Who's in charge out here?

544
00:29:13,518 --> 00:29:15,451
Do you all have a permit?

545
00:29:15,553 --> 00:29:18,213
As long as you don't block
the front of the entrance.

546
00:29:18,323 --> 00:29:20,814
You stay to the side, please. Thank you.

547
00:29:22,925 --> 00:29:26,656
They can walk in front.
The cops have been--

548
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:30,665
As long as you don't block the entrance,
I don't have no problem.

549
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:33,237
They have a FirstAmendment right.

550
00:29:33,336 --> 00:29:35,567
Don't block the entrance.
That's all I'm saying.

551
00:29:35,673 --> 00:29:38,836
It's ringing. I got put in voice mail,
guess they got too many calls.

552
00:29:38,942 --> 00:29:42,001
This one's reaching voice mail.
I'll leave a message.

553
00:29:42,211 --> 00:29:45,478
Hi, this is the protest outside.
Are you guys there?

554
00:29:45,682 --> 00:29:48,083
If you get this, come outside.
We're right down here.

555
00:29:48,184 --> 00:29:49,653
I see someone.

556
00:29:50,153 --> 00:29:53,488
All right. Maybe you'll pick up the phone
or come downstairs later.

557
00:29:53,589 --> 00:29:55,182
You calling the Publicity Department?

558
00:29:55,291 --> 00:29:58,260
No, the main number.
I got a hold of them yesterday...

559
00:29:58,363 --> 00:30:01,161
and I asked for directions to the protest...

560
00:30:01,266 --> 00:30:05,223
and they told me they couldn't get me
from where I was at to here.

561
00:30:05,336 --> 00:30:08,362
I said, ''Okay, I'll call you back tomorrow
when I'm out front.''

562
00:30:08,471 --> 00:30:11,442
-I see them, they've got their heads out.
-There's one.

563
00:30:11,709 --> 00:30:13,106
They're not answering the phones.

564
00:30:13,211 --> 00:30:15,509
Waving banners that said ''Free Kevin''...

565
00:30:15,613 --> 00:30:17,511
and holding ''Stop Miramax'' posters...

566
00:30:17,615 --> 00:30:19,877
the small butvocal crowd of protesters...

567
00:30:19,982 --> 00:30:23,351
stood outside Miramax Pictures'
New York offices yesterday.

568
00:30:23,452 --> 00:30:26,012
At issue: this script, entitled Takedown...

569
00:30:26,124 --> 00:30:30,083
the story of the nation's most notorious
computer hacker, Kevin Mitnick.

570
00:30:30,193 --> 00:30:32,923
Mitnick is currently being held in prison
without bail...

571
00:30:33,029 --> 00:30:35,088
awaiting trial on computer crimes.

572
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:38,226
It's a script these Kevin Mitnick supporters
say is libelous...

573
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:41,066
and would hurt Mitnick's chances
of getting a fair trial.

574
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:43,298
It might influence the jury

575
00:30:43,406 --> 00:30:46,740
It might change a lot of things
in a negative way.

576
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:50,872
He's trying so hard to at least
get a trial and then this comes up...

577
00:30:50,980 --> 00:30:52,914
where he's constantly being defamed.

578
00:30:54,451 --> 00:30:58,682
You never know who you might see
when you're standing outside a film studio.

579
00:30:59,589 --> 00:31:01,923
Kevin Bacon had no interest whatsoever.

580
00:31:04,229 --> 00:31:06,595
But radio personality Lazlow did.

581
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:10,361
With the proliferation of the news...

582
00:31:10,468 --> 00:31:12,798
TV news journalism like Primetime Live...

583
00:31:12,903 --> 00:31:16,567
and these shows
that completely distort the facts...

584
00:31:18,009 --> 00:31:22,944
and shows like 60 Minutes
being forced to go in the same direction...

585
00:31:24,449 --> 00:31:26,314
people don't know the facts about the case.

586
00:31:26,415 --> 00:31:29,682
They don't know the facts about hackers.

587
00:31:30,555 --> 00:31:33,217
I'd say that hackers...

588
00:31:33,691 --> 00:31:35,884
are the communists of the 1990s...

589
00:31:35,992 --> 00:31:39,587
where, basically, if anybody says ''hacker''...

590
00:31:39,695 --> 00:31:43,258
all of a sudden you've got this demon 666 across
your head.

591
00:31:43,366 --> 00:31:45,961
Nobody actually understands any of it.

592
00:31:47,939 --> 00:31:51,534
What I do in my part, on the radio...

593
00:31:52,009 --> 00:31:55,207
with my syndicated show,
is try to get people to open their brains...

594
00:31:55,313 --> 00:31:59,682
because I talk to a lot of old people,
because I'm on a lot of news talk stations.

595
00:31:59,784 --> 00:32:04,242
When I can, I put Emmanuel or Bernie S.,
or anybody else on there...

596
00:32:04,355 --> 00:32:08,414
to talk about the state of what's going on,
because nobody else will cover it.

597
00:32:08,526 --> 00:32:10,685
The people who cover it
in the mainstream media...

598
00:32:10,795 --> 00:32:13,318
do so for profit,
like the guy that wrote the book.

599
00:32:13,431 --> 00:32:17,866
The demonstrators say they have sent
a copy of this illicitly obtained script...

600
00:32:17,969 --> 00:32:21,132
to Kevin Mitnick in jail,
and that he absolutely hates it.

601
00:32:21,239 --> 00:32:24,037
Miramax's parent, Disney,
may not like it either.

602
00:32:24,142 --> 00:32:25,769
The controversy comes on the heels...

603
00:32:25,875 --> 00:32:28,605
of the dumping of $43 million
in Disney stock...

604
00:32:28,711 --> 00:32:30,576
by the Texas Board of Education.

605
00:32:30,682 --> 00:32:34,309
The board's complaint: Miramax films
have too much sex and violence.

606
00:32:34,419 --> 00:32:38,012
Miramax distorts the facts!

607
00:32:42,393 --> 00:32:45,294
Was that Harvey Weinstein,
President of Miramax?

608
00:32:45,394 --> 00:32:46,488
He walked right by us.

609
00:32:46,596 --> 00:32:49,430
He didn't even get
a ''Stop Miramax'' brochure?

610
00:32:49,732 --> 00:32:52,166
Of course we had a brochure for Harvey.

611
00:32:52,501 --> 00:32:54,596
Okay, I'll talk to you later. Bye.

612
00:32:56,272 --> 00:32:58,365
-What did they say?
-I don't know.

613
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:01,508
There she is.
That's the one who answered the phone.

614
00:33:01,612 --> 00:33:03,202
She hung up on me yesterday

615
00:33:03,314 --> 00:33:04,679
I got through.

616
00:33:04,780 --> 00:33:07,114
They waved. Did you see them wave?

617
00:33:07,218 --> 00:33:08,980
Miramax distorts the facts!

618
00:33:09,086 --> 00:33:11,555
They said if you use a bullhorn...

619
00:33:11,654 --> 00:33:15,114
or obstruct people's walkways,
you have to have a permit.

620
00:33:15,259 --> 00:33:17,284
Miramax distorts the facts!

621
00:33:17,626 --> 00:33:20,618
If you continue to use that,
I'm gonna have to call the cops.

622
00:33:23,201 --> 00:33:27,797
I think that three years is a long time
to be held without actually having a trial.

623
00:33:27,939 --> 00:33:30,030
And I think that what Miramax is doing...

624
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:34,601
is going to jeopardize his right
to have a free and honest trial.

625
00:33:35,211 --> 00:33:37,577
So that's why I'm out here protesting.

626
00:33:37,780 --> 00:33:38,942
Thank you.

627
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:44,682
They all were aware of the thing
in front of the building in NewYork City.

628
00:33:44,820 --> 00:33:47,050
They talked about it on the set,
asked me about it.

629
00:33:47,156 --> 00:33:48,750
They said ''Did you talk to Emmanuel?
That's great.''

630
00:33:48,858 --> 00:33:50,759
They were waving. They think it's fantastic.

631
00:33:50,862 --> 00:33:53,557
And they all want Free Kevin stickers.
The whole crew.

632
00:33:53,663 --> 00:33:56,722
If you give me some, I will send it to them.
They will put them on their cars.

633
00:33:56,834 --> 00:33:57,035
Hello, sir.
Do you know who Kevin Mitnick is?

634
00:33:57,035 --> 00:33:59,435
Hello, sir.
Do you know who Kevin Mitnick is?

635
00:33:59,435 --> 00:34:00,596
No, I do not.

636
00:34:00,703 --> 00:34:05,074
Computer hacker who's been in jail
for three-and-a-half years without a trial.

637
00:34:05,276 --> 00:34:07,869
Miramax has decided
to make a movie about him.

638
00:34:07,978 --> 00:34:12,313
The script is false.
It makes him out to be a violent racist...

639
00:34:12,983 --> 00:34:14,280
which he is not.

640
00:34:14,385 --> 00:34:16,284
I want to know what you think about it.

641
00:34:16,387 --> 00:34:17,751
When are they doing the film?

642
00:34:17,855 --> 00:34:20,722
-They start shooting in a few weeks.
-Kevin Mitnick is great.

643
00:34:20,824 --> 00:34:24,317
-How do I find out the truth?
-They should take him out of prison.

644
00:34:24,429 --> 00:34:26,896
-Hold on, I want to talk to you.
-What's that?

645
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:31,434
My main thing is the only reason
he ended up running afoul of the law...

646
00:34:31,536 --> 00:34:34,699
is because people don't have
access to communications.

647
00:34:34,806 --> 00:34:39,436
All you got is big corporations like Miramax
with access to communications.

648
00:34:39,543 --> 00:34:41,375
FirstAmendment! Yeah!

649
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,405
This is inAmerica.

650
00:34:43,514 --> 00:34:46,505
-He was in jail three years without a trial?
-He's still in jail.

651
00:34:46,617 --> 00:34:49,414
I saw something about this
on CNBC on Friday.

652
00:34:49,518 --> 00:34:51,181
This happens a lot, though.

653
00:34:51,289 --> 00:34:55,349
You always have unauthorized biographies
and stuff like that.

654
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:57,690
Where it's like, you have an autobiography...

655
00:34:57,795 --> 00:35:00,059
you have an authorized biography.

656
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:04,099
-This is sort of like an unauthorized--
-This is going to be big.

657
00:35:04,202 --> 00:35:07,068
-He hasn't had a trial yet?
-Hasn't had a trial yet.

658
00:35:07,572 --> 00:35:11,668
Not only that, in the movie,
they already wrote that he had a trial.

659
00:35:12,409 --> 00:35:15,469
-You ever hear of Kevin Mitnick?
-No. Who's that?

660
00:35:15,579 --> 00:35:18,708
Well, if you're walking away, I really can't....

661
00:35:20,818 --> 00:35:23,581
How did you guys get a hold of the script?

662
00:35:24,021 --> 00:35:25,579
Okay. All right.

663
00:35:28,893 --> 00:35:32,454
You're a lawyer.
Isn't it illegal if they're gonna slander him?

664
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:35,030
Can't they try and stop them
on legal grounds?

665
00:35:35,132 --> 00:35:37,623
That's not right.They have to put a waiver--

666
00:35:37,735 --> 00:35:41,465
I think they should hold the film
until after he's had a fair trial.

667
00:35:41,873 --> 00:35:44,273
I mean, it happens.
It happened, unfortunately

668
00:35:44,375 --> 00:35:46,137
You know, I don't think it should be....

669
00:35:46,244 --> 00:35:50,043
Obviously, it's probably not legal
to have a lawsuit against Miramax.

670
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:53,583
I think they should have to wait
until he's had a fair trial.

671
00:35:53,684 --> 00:35:55,652
And also they shouldn't use his real name.

672
00:35:55,753 --> 00:35:58,585
If they want to change the facts,
they should change the name.

673
00:35:58,688 --> 00:36:01,885
-Make it a fictional story.
-Three-and-a-half years is a long time.

674
00:36:01,992 --> 00:36:05,224
Think about what you've done
for the last three-and-a-half years.

675
00:36:05,329 --> 00:36:09,766
And imagine being in jail
while all that stuff was happening.

676
00:36:10,501 --> 00:36:14,766
For just that. Just for copying software.

677
00:36:15,672 --> 00:36:17,163
I've copied software.

678
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:19,931
-What did he do? He hacked.
-He hacked.

679
00:36:20,311 --> 00:36:22,175
I would like to know your opinion...

680
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:25,681
on the slandering in this film.

681
00:36:28,418 --> 00:36:31,181
Miramax sucks. So, like, Free Kevin!

682
00:36:34,791 --> 00:36:38,523
I can't talk shit about a movie
I haven't seen or read the script of.

683
00:36:39,197 --> 00:36:41,630
But the one relevant thing that I could say..

684
00:36:41,731 --> 00:36:45,963
is it seems to me there is
a witch-hunt sort of hysterical mentality..

685
00:36:46,070 --> 00:36:48,061
vis-a-vis hacking, you know.

686
00:36:48,172 --> 00:36:52,074
People are very quick to fly off the handle
and condemn as terrorists...

687
00:36:52,577 --> 00:36:56,445
people who are, you know,
exploring a newtechnology landscape...

688
00:36:56,547 --> 00:36:58,708
in a way that they don't understand.

689
00:36:58,983 --> 00:37:02,009
-Definitely.
-That's as far as I can go not having seen it.

690
00:37:02,119 --> 00:37:04,882
Not only did we find a receptive bunch
at local theaters...

691
00:37:04,989 --> 00:37:06,980
they even started to do our work for us.

692
00:37:07,090 --> 00:37:09,559
New York was great.
But it was only the start.

693
00:37:09,559 --> 00:37:10,360
New York was great.
But it was only the start.

694
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:14,422
We had to travel to get to the right people.
So we put together a camera crew...

695
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:18,092
and made sure none of us had anything
planned for the next several weeks.

696
00:37:18,202 --> 00:37:21,103
We charted out a course,
and headed to the airport.

697
00:37:21,204 --> 00:37:24,663
That's where we got our economy-sized
rental car with unlimited mileage.

698
00:37:24,775 --> 00:37:27,175
The plan was to go
to Wilmington, North Carolina...

699
00:37:27,277 --> 00:37:29,576
where filming for Takedown
was about to begin.

700
00:37:29,679 --> 00:37:32,648
On the way, we figured we'd make a detour
and stop at Defcon...

701
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,945
the annual hacker convention in Las Vegas.

702
00:37:35,052 --> 00:37:37,748
If we were going to do that,
we should stop in San Diego...

703
00:37:37,855 --> 00:37:39,413
to say hi to Tsutomu Shimomura...

704
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:42,617
and maybe convince him
to stop using Kevin Mitnick as a cash cow.

705
00:37:42,726 --> 00:37:45,695
And if we did that,
it would be rude not to visit John Markof...

706
00:37:45,795 --> 00:37:49,253
to ask him to inject some accuracy
into his stories about Kevin.

707
00:37:49,367 --> 00:37:52,494
Since we were suddenly adding
10,000 miles to this rental car...

708
00:37:52,603 --> 00:37:54,764
we might as well visit
some of the corporations...

709
00:37:54,871 --> 00:37:58,431
