Maybe they'll call back, maybe they won't.

1412
01:19:33,201 --> 01:19:36,033
This is the red hotline.
If that rings, we'll know

1413
01:19:37,706 --> 01:19:39,332
We have GPS, good.

1414
01:19:39,841 --> 01:19:41,934
GPS but no modem. Man, that sucks.

1415
01:19:43,612 --> 01:19:47,069
I was using it last night and it was gone
in the morning which means....

1416
01:19:47,180 --> 01:19:49,444
Sorry, no cameras in front of the building.

1417
01:19:49,551 --> 01:19:51,576
How about if we film in that direction?

1418
01:19:52,453 --> 01:19:54,216
We can't have the cameras filming.

1419
01:19:54,322 --> 01:19:56,288
Okay, 'cause we were just filming us.

1420
01:19:56,390 --> 01:19:59,359
No, I can understand that,
but unfortunately...

1421
01:19:59,694 --> 01:20:01,184
Wow, this was a new one.

1422
01:20:01,296 --> 01:20:04,322
We couldn't even film ourselves
in Sun's parking lot.

1423
01:20:04,497 --> 01:20:07,332
Corporate paranoia was at an all-time high.

1424
01:20:07,469 --> 01:20:10,493
And, needless to say,
Pete never called us back.

1425
01:20:10,770 --> 01:20:11,604
Meanwhile, John Markoff
had agreed to talk to us.

1426
01:20:11,604 --> 01:20:13,506
Meanwhile, John Markoff
had agreed to talk to us.

1427
01:20:13,506 --> 01:20:15,635
Maybe now we'd finally get some answers.

1428
01:20:16,077 --> 01:20:18,545
We made it to San Francisco
on the exact same day...

1429
01:20:18,645 --> 01:20:21,739
that psychologists from around the world
gathered for a convention.

1430
01:20:21,850 --> 01:20:24,375
Maybe because so many people
in that area were depressed.

1431
01:20:24,484 --> 01:20:26,420
They have counseling phones
on the bridges...

1432
01:20:26,520 --> 01:20:28,546
because so many people
are jumping off them.

1433
01:20:28,657 --> 01:20:30,350
But San Francisco was a friendly town...

1434
01:20:30,457 --> 01:20:33,484
where people felt safe
leaving their trash unattended.

1435
01:20:33,828 --> 01:20:35,296
But more importantly...

1436
01:20:35,662 --> 01:20:40,158
the psychologists wound up taking
almost every hotel room in the entire city...

1437
01:20:43,069 --> 01:20:45,162
even the old-fashioned ones.

1438
01:20:47,841 --> 01:20:50,310
We were beginning to get desperate.

1439
01:20:52,011 --> 01:20:55,676
Then we found a hotel
that was almost completely deserted.

1440
01:20:55,783 --> 01:20:57,216
We never did find out why.

1441
01:20:59,688 --> 01:21:02,417
Markoff mentions certain stories.

1442
01:21:02,524 --> 01:21:06,426
He'll say, ''lt's been said that....''
or ''Other people have said that....''

1443
01:21:06,528 --> 01:21:11,328
And he'll come up with these stories
like he shut down judges'TRW ratings...

1444
01:21:11,431 --> 01:21:13,264
shut off power.... It's bullshit.

1445
01:21:13,734 --> 01:21:18,604
I don't think John Markoff
did it because he wanted to destroy Kevin.

1446
01:21:18,872 --> 01:21:23,002
But I think he did it
to keep Kevin's evil image.

1447
01:21:23,109 --> 01:21:25,408
Maybe he believed
some of the things himself.

1448
01:21:25,881 --> 01:21:27,814
Okay, isn't a newspaperman...

1449
01:21:27,916 --> 01:21:31,975
supposed to investigate something
before they publish it...

1450
01:21:32,118 --> 01:21:34,747
before they put it in the newspaper as fact?

1451
01:21:35,256 --> 01:21:38,658
I know Spencer Tracy
and Clark Gable always did.

1452
01:21:42,363 --> 01:21:46,960
We didn't know what we were walking into.
Would Markoff tell us things about Mitnick...

1453
01:21:47,068 --> 01:21:49,662
that would shock and horrify us?
Or would he realize...

1454
01:21:49,770 --> 01:21:52,706
how much his front-page stories
and books had demonized Kevin...

1455
01:21:52,805 --> 01:21:55,569
helping to put him in the lousy place
he was still in?

1456
01:21:55,676 --> 01:21:57,667
This was our one chance
to make a difference.

1457
01:21:58,313 --> 01:22:01,212
And, more than anything,
we wanted to be fair.

1458
01:22:01,614 --> 01:22:05,484
So we came up with the Markoff Meter.
We set a bar on his left and right side...

1459
01:22:05,587 --> 01:22:09,386
and resolved not to judge him badly
until he said six bad or inaccurate things.

1460
01:22:09,489 --> 01:22:11,185
And if he said six good things...

1461
01:22:11,292 --> 01:22:14,194
well, then, the hacker world
would just have to deal with it.

1462
01:22:15,962 --> 01:22:18,158
Maybe this wouldn't be so bad.

1463
01:22:22,404 --> 01:22:24,529
Nowthere's an easy point
for common courtesy.

1464
01:22:26,105 --> 01:22:28,096
I wanted to get to the heart of the matter

1465
01:22:28,207 --> 01:22:32,077
Like howthey knew it was Kevin
they were chasing in the first place?

1466
01:22:33,148 --> 01:22:36,777
When I called the Qualcomm guys,
they had been talking to the FBI.

1467
01:22:36,885 --> 01:22:40,514
And the FBI believed that it was Kevin
who had social engineered them.

1468
01:22:40,622 --> 01:22:41,609
Why?

1469
01:22:43,823 --> 01:22:47,020
I don't know enough
about what was going on...

1470
01:22:47,127 --> 01:22:48,755
inside the FBI investigation.

1471
01:22:49,162 --> 01:22:51,756
That's a good question. I don't know why

1472
01:22:51,864 --> 01:22:55,461
But the FBI told the Qualcomm people
that it was Kevin.

1473
01:22:55,636 --> 01:22:58,399
And, to my mind, as a reporter,
it fit Kevin's M.O.

1474
01:22:58,506 --> 01:23:00,804
-Which is what?
-Social engineering.

1475
01:23:00,908 --> 01:23:02,238
Really good social engineering.

1476
01:23:02,344 --> 01:23:04,470
But there are thousands
of hackers out there--

1477
01:23:04,578 --> 01:23:06,103
That's true.

1478
01:23:06,514 --> 01:23:08,345
I'm not saying it's proof.

1479
01:23:08,448 --> 01:23:10,814
I'm simply saying
the FBI believed it was Kevin.

1480
01:23:11,586 --> 01:23:14,817
Did they hear a voice
or did they have a voice recording?

1481
01:23:15,657 --> 01:23:19,649
Did they have a voice recording?
That's a good question. What did they have?

1482
01:23:19,761 --> 01:23:21,319
This we couldn't forgive.

1483
01:23:21,429 --> 01:23:25,229
Before you print front-page stories
about people eluding the authorities...

1484
01:23:25,332 --> 01:23:27,663
shouldn't you have
some real conclusive evidence?

1485
01:23:28,935 --> 01:23:30,564
What did Kevin do that was diferent?

1486
01:23:30,671 --> 01:23:33,800
He had a reputation
as being a very good social engineer.

1487
01:23:35,310 --> 01:23:38,506
I've heard some tapes,
I've heard some people assert this.

1488
01:23:39,581 --> 01:23:43,140
If he in fact was the person
who was at Qualcomm...

1489
01:23:43,251 --> 01:23:45,377
then he was a good social engineer.

1490
01:23:47,188 --> 01:23:50,988
Nowthat's better. No need to be stingy
with the compliments, after all.

1491
01:23:51,091 --> 01:23:53,287
One thing that's been following
Kevin Mitnick...

1492
01:23:53,395 --> 01:23:58,094
since the first story Markoff wrote about him
is this myth about breaking into NORAD.

1493
01:23:58,198 --> 01:24:02,158
When you say something like that
enough times, people start to believe it.

1494
01:24:02,502 --> 01:24:05,529
And in Kevin's case,
it really made him into a villain.

1495
01:24:06,172 --> 01:24:08,573
So where did the NORAD stuff come from?

1496
01:24:09,176 --> 01:24:10,542
The NORAD stuff...

1497
01:24:11,179 --> 01:24:14,046
is stuff that I got from someone...

1498
01:24:14,149 --> 01:24:16,672
who was in legal trouble
with Kevin early on.

1499
01:24:17,051 --> 01:24:21,546
So I have not been able to interview Kevin
face to face.

1500
01:24:21,654 --> 01:24:25,353
I've heard he said that it's inaccurate
but I haven't been able to ask him.

1501
01:24:25,460 --> 01:24:27,826
The story did come from a friend of his.

1502
01:24:28,063 --> 01:24:31,658
I know there are lots of stories
and you gotta sort through them.

1503
01:24:32,332 --> 01:24:34,301
But what stories have stuck?

1504
01:24:34,402 --> 01:24:38,734
I remember the Kristy McNichol thing.
That didn't stick. NORAD didn't stick.

1505
01:24:38,840 --> 01:24:43,470
Security Pacific I think is probably one
that stuck, that probably should stick.

1506
01:24:43,645 --> 01:24:46,671
-You know about that?
-The bank that he got a job at--

1507
01:24:46,779 --> 01:24:49,341
That's right.
And then there was a press release...

1508
01:24:49,451 --> 01:24:52,180
that suggested that the bank
was in financial trouble...

1509
01:24:52,287 --> 01:24:55,188
though they managed to keep it of the wire,
it almost went on.

1510
01:24:55,288 --> 01:24:57,154
But what links that to Kevin?

1511
01:24:57,256 --> 01:25:01,056
The police investigators that we interviewed
believed it was Kevin.

1512
01:25:01,229 --> 01:25:02,694
Based on what?

1513
01:25:06,332 --> 01:25:07,801
Based on what....

1514
01:25:08,770 --> 01:25:11,931
Just coincidence of things.
Who else would do something like that?

1515
01:25:13,274 --> 01:25:14,969
You've got to be kidding!

1516
01:25:15,176 --> 01:25:17,609
You used ''who else''
to pin a crime on the guy...

1517
01:25:17,712 --> 01:25:19,542
on the front page of the NewYork Times...

1518
01:25:19,645 --> 01:25:22,274
without even using
the word ''allegedly'' anywhere?

1519
01:25:22,381 --> 01:25:25,113
This was reported as fact
but it was never backed up.

1520
01:25:25,220 --> 01:25:27,484
Just like NORAD, just like Kristy McNichol...

1521
01:25:27,587 --> 01:25:30,988
just like everything that made them
want to catch Kevin so badly.

1522
01:25:31,091 --> 01:25:33,492
Let's look at the issue
of solitary confinement.

1523
01:25:33,595 --> 01:25:35,654
It wasn't mentioned
in the front-page article...

1524
01:25:35,761 --> 01:25:39,390
that Kevin was in solitary for 8 months
and was desperate not to go back...

1525
01:25:39,501 --> 01:25:42,229
and that this above all
was what made him run.

1526
01:25:42,337 --> 01:25:44,805
I mean, he didn't want to go back to jail.

1527
01:25:44,904 --> 01:25:47,372
Not just jail, solitary confinement.
Eight months.

1528
01:25:47,475 --> 01:25:49,943
Was he in solitary before?
This was his first time.

1529
01:25:50,042 --> 01:25:51,203
1989.

1530
01:25:51,377 --> 01:25:54,109
He spent 8 months in solitary in 1989?
I didn't realize.

1531
01:25:54,215 --> 01:25:58,618
Wait. He didn't spend 8 months in prison.
He was only in prison for six months in '89.

1532
01:26:00,121 --> 01:26:03,247
You've written two books on the guy
as well as countless articles.

1533
01:26:03,358 --> 01:26:05,417
You're somewhat of an expert
on Kevin Mitnick...

1534
01:26:05,527 --> 01:26:07,893
and you didn't know
he was in solitary confinement?

1535
01:26:07,996 --> 01:26:10,122
Or even how long his sentence was?

1536
01:26:10,229 --> 01:26:13,426
For the record, Mitnick spent a year
in prison in 1988...

1537
01:26:13,533 --> 01:26:15,899
eight months of which
was in solitary confinement...

1538
01:26:16,002 --> 01:26:18,493
plus another six months in a halfway house.

1539
01:26:18,971 --> 01:26:21,462
With the psychologists in town
we could confirm...

1540
01:26:21,576 --> 01:26:24,636
locking Kevin in solitary
was a fucked-up thing to do.

1541
01:26:28,814 --> 01:26:33,014
I think it's inhumane, and I think there are
better ways to handle our problems.

1542
01:26:33,121 --> 01:26:36,783
Obviously if this person has been able
to do some of the things...

1543
01:26:36,890 --> 01:26:40,292
that they think he was doing
with a computer, he's very bright.

1544
01:26:40,395 --> 01:26:42,828
That's a real talent that's being wasted.

1545
01:26:43,162 --> 01:26:47,189
And, to lock him up, especially
in solitary confinement for 8 months....

1546
01:26:47,301 --> 01:26:49,532
We wouldn't treat an animal that way

1547
01:26:49,871 --> 01:26:53,203
And yet, this is a talented individual?
Excuse me.

1548
01:26:54,175 --> 01:26:56,573
- It's not right. Thank you.
- Thanks very much.

1549
01:26:56,911 --> 01:26:59,778
Wait, he was in solitary
the entire time he was at Lompoc?

1550
01:26:59,881 --> 01:27:02,247
A large amount of the time. Eight months.

1551
01:27:03,051 --> 01:27:04,746
Yeah, that's pretty hard.

1552
01:27:06,654 --> 01:27:10,145
Okay. Markoff gains a point
for that show of humanity.

1553
01:27:10,756 --> 01:27:13,988
Now, here's something interesting.
When Kevin was on the run...

1554
01:27:14,095 --> 01:27:17,426
he communicated with an Israeli hacker
known as jsz...

1555
01:27:17,532 --> 01:27:21,729
who's believed to be the mastermind behind
the hacking that Kevin was blamed for.

1556
01:27:21,836 --> 01:27:24,270
Yet Markoff never wrote a story about him...

1557
01:27:24,372 --> 01:27:27,500
and didn't even followthrough
when jsz moved to New York.

1558
01:27:27,609 --> 01:27:30,337
In fact, none of the authorities
seemed to care either...

1559
01:27:30,444 --> 01:27:33,005
almost as if these crimes were really trivial.

1560
01:27:33,113 --> 01:27:36,140
Nowthat would be a great story,
wouldn't it, John?

1561
01:27:36,417 --> 01:27:38,180
I thought a lot about that.

1562
01:27:38,453 --> 01:27:43,152
I just haven't had time to do the reporting.
I've got a day-to-day beat out here.

1563
01:27:43,725 --> 01:27:47,091
You're right. It's probably a great story
I would love to talk to jsz.

1564
01:27:47,194 --> 01:27:50,528
-I should come to New York--
-That story was going on back then.

1565
01:27:50,631 --> 01:27:54,225
Jsz was supposedly the mastermind
behind everything.

1566
01:27:54,667 --> 01:27:56,569
I never knew what the relations were.

1567
01:27:56,671 --> 01:27:59,604
The only thing I could say that I knew..

1568
01:27:59,707 --> 01:28:03,143
was that jsz and Kevin...

1569
01:28:03,243 --> 01:28:05,734
were actively trading
information and software.

1570
01:28:05,845 --> 01:28:09,840
That's what I knew.
I knew nothing about masterminding.

1571
01:28:11,719 --> 01:28:15,154
If you asked me
to reconstruct just from what I knew..

1572
01:28:15,256 --> 01:28:18,555
it was jsz provided the tools
and Kevin made the attack.

1573
01:28:18,658 --> 01:28:20,127
But I have no idea if that's true.

1574
01:28:21,560 --> 01:28:22,788
No idea?

1575
01:28:23,331 --> 01:28:28,198
Isn't this what the book, series of articles,
and nowthe film are supposedly based on...

1576
01:28:28,301 --> 01:28:30,237
what Kevin actually did?

1577
01:28:30,805 --> 01:28:33,296
I was amazed by what he didn't know

1578
01:28:33,573 --> 01:28:37,237
But there was more that he did know
and had never talked about before.

1579
01:28:37,345 --> 01:28:40,371
But one interesting thing
that hasn't been made public.

1580
01:28:40,613 --> 01:28:44,413
You know, so much was made of the fact
that the credit cards were never used.

1581
01:28:44,519 --> 01:28:45,917
They were used.

1582
01:28:46,453 --> 01:28:49,319
An American Express card,
part of the Netcom collection...

1583
01:28:49,422 --> 01:28:53,917
was used in Raleigh within two days
after Kevin was arrested.

1584
01:28:55,229 --> 01:28:56,489
So who used it?

1585
01:28:56,595 --> 01:29:00,087
-How did you find this out?
-I've just known it for a long time.

1586
01:29:00,399 --> 01:29:02,698
You're saying the credit card
was used in Raleigh...

1587
01:29:02,804 --> 01:29:05,238
and it was used after he was arrested?

1588
01:29:05,340 --> 01:29:09,242
There are indications that there was
someone Kevin was in contact with...

1589
01:29:09,344 --> 01:29:12,541
who knewthis and may have been
active in the Raleigh area.

1590
01:29:12,645 --> 01:29:15,411
All I'm saying is there's some evidence.

1591
01:29:15,515 --> 01:29:17,279
How come this wasn't in the book?

1592
01:29:17,385 --> 01:29:19,376
How come it wasn't in the book.
Good question.

1593
01:29:19,487 --> 01:29:21,819
I don't know why
we didn't put it in the book.

1594
01:29:23,157 --> 01:29:24,783
This was really getting annoying.

1595
01:29:24,890 --> 01:29:27,952
He didn't follow up on
the most interesting part of the story..

1596
01:29:28,060 --> 01:29:31,259
and he didn't mention the fact
about the credit cards until now?

1597
01:29:31,364 --> 01:29:34,301
One more remark like that
and it's all over for Markoff.

1598
01:29:36,770 --> 01:29:40,364
Look how many people are standing here
and not one person took my brochure.

1599
01:29:40,475 --> 01:29:43,706
Look at all these people.
Not one of them took this.

1600
01:29:45,145 --> 01:29:46,670
Valuable coupons!

1601
01:29:48,015 --> 01:29:49,676
What are they doing now?

1602
01:29:50,051 --> 01:29:52,519
Oh, Kevin Mitnick!
He's the computer wizard.

1603
01:29:52,618 --> 01:29:56,112
The way that the Japanese wizard
found him was very interesting.

1604
01:29:56,422 --> 01:29:59,689
Mitnick respected the Japanese wizard
for tracking him.

1605
01:29:59,792 --> 01:30:00,988
On the other hand...

1606
01:30:01,095 --> 01:30:04,756
since the whole computer business
is stupid and ridiculous to begin with...

1607
01:30:04,864 --> 01:30:09,166
why should Mitnick suffer
for a ridiculous assault on the culture...

1608
01:30:09,301 --> 01:30:11,635
namely the computer. So that's it.

1609
01:30:11,738 --> 01:30:13,796
-What do you think of computers?
-I hate them.

1610
01:30:13,908 --> 01:30:14,895
Why?

1611
01:30:15,341 --> 01:30:20,176
Because they're not like feeling skin,
and they're not like walking in the forest.

1612
01:30:20,546 --> 01:30:23,711
And one can get lost deeply in them.

1613
01:30:23,818 --> 01:30:26,546
My son, of course, is in that world.

1614
01:30:26,854 --> 01:30:31,221
These people are computerphiles
and he's a computerphobe.

1615
01:30:31,390 --> 01:30:35,158
Hackers are all right
because they're anarchists, that's fine.

1616
01:30:35,261 --> 01:30:37,127
But the rest of it....

1617
01:30:37,863 --> 01:30:39,797
-This is bullshit.
-lt's pornography!

1618
01:30:39,899 --> 01:30:41,368
This is such bullshit!

1619
01:30:41,469 --> 01:30:43,993
I like Chaos Computer Club, I like anarchy.

1620
01:30:44,104 --> 01:30:46,435
- You know Chaos Computer Club?
- No, but I like the whole idea.

1621
01:30:46,541 --> 01:30:48,475
He's never heard of it.
He's saying this because--

1622
01:30:48,576 --> 01:30:51,600
No, it's great. But Mitnick, it's ridiculous.

1623
01:30:52,613 --> 01:30:53,978
Look, an activist.

1624
01:30:56,117 --> 01:30:58,176
Look, a bag of artificial intelligence.

1625
01:30:58,286 --> 01:31:02,220
They're from the '80s but I still bought them.
Just to get back to my roots.

1626
01:31:02,323 --> 01:31:05,759
It's like the government's
making him look like....

1627
01:31:05,859 --> 01:31:10,591
It's to create a hacker mythology so
they can deprive other people of privacy...

1628
01:31:10,698 --> 01:31:11,858
and other stuff like that.

1629
01:31:11,966 --> 01:31:15,832
He hasn't done anything wrong. He hasn't
done any financial damage to anybody

1630
01:31:15,935 --> 01:31:18,131
He's basically just like a scapegoat.

1631
01:31:18,238 --> 01:31:22,073
I think most of the kids that I hang out with
are cool, geeky, hacker types.

1632
01:31:22,176 --> 01:31:26,112
They understand.
Then there's my mom and everybody else.

1633
01:31:26,212 --> 01:31:29,181
Why would they have any reason
to believe anything...

1634
01:31:29,283 --> 01:31:31,478
other than he's a total scumbag who....

1635
01:31:31,586 --> 01:31:34,520
You know, like WarGames, the hacking.

1636
01:31:34,787 --> 01:31:38,189
That guy! Didn't he break into
massive computer systems?

1637
01:31:38,292 --> 01:31:41,819
He's not accused of selling information,
